<ReportItem port="22" svc_name="ssh" protocol="tcp" severity="2" pluginID="187315" pluginName="SSH Terrapin Prefix Truncation Weakness (CVE-2023-48795)" pluginFamily="Misc.">
<age_of_vuln>730 days +</age_of_vuln>
<cpe>cpe:/a:openbsd:openssh</cpe>
<cve>CVE-2023-48795</cve>
<cvss3_base_score>5.9</cvss3_base_score>
<cvss3_temporal_score>5.3</cvss3_temporal_score>
<cvss3_temporal_vector>CVSS:3.0/E:P/RL:O/RC:C</cvss3_temporal_vector>
<cvss3_vector>CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:H/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:N</cvss3_vector>
<cvssV3_impactScore>3.6</cvssV3_impactScore>
<cvss_base_score>5.4</cvss_base_score>
<cvss_score_source>CVE-2023-48795</cvss_score_source>
<cvss_temporal_score>4.2</cvss_temporal_score>
<cvss_temporal_vector>CVSS2#E:POC/RL:OF/RC:C</cvss_temporal_vector>
<cvss_vector>CVSS2#AV:N/AC:H/Au:N/C:N/I:C/A:N</cvss_vector>
<description>The remote SSH server is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle prefix truncation weakness known as Terrapin. This can allow a remote, man-in-the-middle attacker to bypass integrity checks and downgrade the connection&apos;s security.

Note that this plugin only checks for remote SSH servers that support either ChaCha20-Poly1305 or CBC with Encrypt-then-MAC and do not support the strict key exchange countermeasures. It does not check for vulnerable software versions.</description>
<epss_score>0.5786</epss_score>
<exploit_available>true</exploit_available>
<exploit_code_maturity>PoC</exploit_code_maturity>
<exploitability_ease>Exploits are available</exploitability_ease>
<fname>ssh_terrapin_weakness.nasl</fname>
<patch_publication_date>2023/12/18</patch_publication_date>
<plugin_modification_date>2026/01/12</plugin_modification_date>
<plugin_name>SSH Terrapin Prefix Truncation Weakness (CVE-2023-48795)</plugin_name>
<plugin_publication_date>2023/12/27</plugin_publication_date>
<plugin_type>remote</plugin_type>
<product_coverage>Very High</product_coverage>
<risk_factor>Medium</risk_factor>
<script_version>1.5</script_version>
<see_also>https://terrapin-attack.com/</see_also>
<solution>Contact the vendor for an update with the strict key exchange countermeasures or disable the affected algorithms.</solution>
<synopsis>The remote SSH server is vulnerable to a mitm prefix truncation attack.</synopsis>
<threat_intensity_last_28>Very Low</threat_intensity_last_28>
<threat_recency>No recorded events</threat_recency>
<threat_sources_last_28>No recorded events</threat_sources_last_28>
<vpr_score>6.7</vpr_score>
<vuln_publication_date>2023/12/18</vuln_publication_date>
